                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>\n                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\"><persName>Mr Selling</persName> called<lb/> for your books and has\n                them now in<lb/> his possession. He requested me to state<lb/> that the society is\n                unwilling to defray<lb/> my expense <del>oc</del>incurred. It is his intention<lb/>\n                to keep the books for a time to see<lb/> if he can get customers. If he cannot<lb/>\n                he will return them. The people of <placeName>Hartford</placeName><lb/> will buy\n                anything in preference to books.<lb/> I perceive from the paper that <persName>Soln\n                    Jacobs</persName><lb/> is about to quit <placeName>Charleston</placeName>. I\n                would like to know why. Do you think I would<lb/> have any chance there as lecturer\n                Teacher<lb/> &amp;cYours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">A Harris</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <date>June 18 1857</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>The particulars of the murder of <persName>Jackson</persName><lb/> are these. There\n                were three brothers two<lb/> of whom were in partnership &amp; kept a store<lb/> The\n                kind a youth of 17 peddled for the<lb/> former. The young men were all good<lb/>\n                <add>יהודים</add> did no business on <add>שבת</add> or <add>יום טוב</add><lb/> about\n                afortnight before the murder</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3x05xz9b/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
